[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:01:55.215 --> 00:02:03.400 align:middle line:90%


00:02:03.400 --> 00:02:04.210 align:middle line:90%
So here we are.

00:02:04.210 --> 00:02:05.840 align:middle line:90%
We're in the fourth question.

00:02:05.840 --> 00:02:08.990 align:middle line:84%
The fourth question is,
where do we go from here?

00:02:08.990 --> 00:02:10.960 align:middle line:84%
And let's use this
as an opportunity

00:02:10.960 --> 00:02:14.200 align:middle line:84%
to explore what each of us
can do, maybe what we can do

00:02:14.200 --> 00:02:17.160 align:middle line:84%
individually and what
we can do together

00:02:17.160 --> 00:02:19.300 align:middle line:84%
in this great work of
changing the direction

00:02:19.300 --> 00:02:21.170 align:middle line:90%
of the human family.

00:02:21.170 --> 00:02:23.270 align:middle line:84%
We're going to start
by looking at what

00:02:23.270 --> 00:02:25.220 align:middle line:90%
it means to take a stand.

00:02:25.220 --> 00:02:27.240 align:middle line:84%
And we've got a
video that will give

00:02:27.240 --> 00:02:32.410 align:middle line:84%
some wonderful illustrations
of the power of a stand.

00:02:32.410 --> 00:02:35.700 align:middle line:90%
It's 3:23 in the morning.

00:02:35.700 --> 00:02:37.680 align:middle line:10%
And I'm awake.

00:02:37.680 --> 00:02:40.890 align:middle line:10%
Because my great,
great grandchildren

00:02:40.890 --> 00:02:43.020 align:middle line:10%
won't let me sleep.

00:02:43.020 --> 00:02:46.770 align:middle line:84%
My great, great
grandchildren ask me

00:02:46.770 --> 00:02:53.730 align:middle line:84%
in dreams, what did you do
while the planet was plundered?

00:02:53.730 --> 00:02:58.060 align:middle line:84%
What did you do when the
earth was unraveling?

00:02:58.060 --> 00:03:00.420 align:middle line:84%
Surely you did something
when the seasons

00:03:00.420 --> 00:03:08.150 align:middle line:84%
started failing, as the mammals,
reptiles, birds were all dying.

00:03:08.150 --> 00:03:10.630 align:middle line:84%
Did you fill the
streets with protest

00:03:10.630 --> 00:03:13.150 align:middle line:90%
when democracy was stolen?

00:03:13.150 --> 00:03:17.842 align:middle line:90%
What did you do once you knew?

00:03:17.842 --> 00:03:21.670 align:middle line:90%


00:03:21.670 --> 00:03:23.840 align:middle line:90%
So now we know.

00:03:23.840 --> 00:03:26.700 align:middle line:10%
We know that our current world
view and the industrial system

00:03:26.700 --> 00:03:29.300 align:middle line:10%
it gave rise to have run
up against the limits

00:03:29.300 --> 00:03:30.230 align:middle line:10%
of a finite planet.

00:03:30.230 --> 00:03:32.800 align:middle line:90%


00:03:32.800 --> 00:03:34.490 align:middle line:84%
We know that the
vitality of the earth

00:03:34.490 --> 00:03:38.650 align:middle line:84%
is declining every day, that the
chasm between the few of us who

00:03:38.650 --> 00:03:41.580 align:middle line:84%
have more than we need and the
many of us who have not nearly

00:03:41.580 --> 00:03:46.270 align:middle line:90%
enough gets wider every day.

00:03:46.270 --> 00:03:50.960 align:middle line:84%
And we know that it is
hurting all of us inside.

00:03:50.960 --> 00:03:52.950 align:middle line:84%
At the same time,
we knew that we

00:03:52.950 --> 00:03:55.630 align:middle line:84%
are part of a
worldwide awakening,

00:03:55.630 --> 00:03:58.080 align:middle line:84%
a grassroots movement
for change that is

00:03:58.080 --> 00:04:01.950 align:middle line:90%
unprecedented in human history.

00:04:01.950 --> 00:04:05.200 align:middle line:84%
So now that we know,
the question arises,

00:04:05.200 --> 00:04:09.750 align:middle line:84%
what part do we play in
this great unfolding story?

00:04:09.750 --> 00:04:12.510 align:middle line:90%
Where do we go from here?

00:04:12.510 --> 00:04:14.684 align:middle line:90%
Where do you go from here?

00:04:14.684 --> 00:04:19.076 align:middle line:90%


00:04:19.076 --> 00:04:21.519 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING]

00:04:21.519 --> 00:05:54.430 align:middle line:90%


00:05:54.430 --> 00:05:56.450 align:middle line:90%
People want to know what to do.

00:05:56.450 --> 00:05:57.960 align:middle line:10%
And I think that's a
good question, too.

00:05:57.960 --> 00:06:00.580 align:middle line:10%
But a more profound question
and a more powerful question

00:06:00.580 --> 00:06:02.420 align:middle line:10%
is, who do we need to be?

00:06:02.420 --> 00:06:05.550 align:middle line:10%
And I think who we need
to be are people who

00:06:05.550 --> 00:06:09.310 align:middle line:10%
know that the decisions
and choices we make now

00:06:09.310 --> 00:06:12.780 align:middle line:10%
impact the future of life
for the next 100 years.

00:06:12.780 --> 00:06:16.680 align:middle line:84%
Everybody alive today
has a role to play.

00:06:16.680 --> 00:06:19.400 align:middle line:84%
You don't have a big role and
you don't have a small role,

00:06:19.400 --> 00:06:21.100 align:middle line:90%
you just have your role.

00:06:21.100 --> 00:06:24.490 align:middle line:84%
And if you play
it, then your life

00:06:24.490 --> 00:06:28.410 align:middle line:84%
will really have a kind of
meaning that you've dreamt of.

00:06:28.410 --> 00:06:31.200 align:middle line:90%


00:06:31.200 --> 00:06:33.830 align:middle line:10%
This is the true joy in life.

00:06:33.830 --> 00:06:36.550 align:middle line:10%
The being used for
a purpose recognized

00:06:36.550 --> 00:06:39.090 align:middle line:10%
by yourself as a mighty one.

00:06:39.090 --> 00:06:39.805 align:middle line:10%
[SPEAKING IN FRENCH]

00:06:39.805 --> 00:06:44.550 align:middle line:90%


00:06:44.550 --> 00:06:46.560 align:middle line:10%
Complaining that the
world will not devote

00:06:46.560 --> 00:06:48.827 align:middle line:10%
itself to making you happy.

00:06:48.827 --> 00:06:49.560 align:middle line:10%
[SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

00:06:49.560 --> 00:06:53.420 align:middle line:90%


00:06:53.420 --> 00:06:57.250 align:middle line:10%
And for as long as I
live, it is my privilege

00:06:57.250 --> 00:07:00.230 align:middle line:10%
to do for it whatever I can.

00:07:00.230 --> 00:07:03.550 align:middle line:10%
I want to be thoroughly
used up when I die.

00:07:03.550 --> 00:07:04.615 align:middle line:10%
For the harder I work--

00:07:04.615 --> 00:07:07.170 align:middle line:10%
The more I live.

00:07:07.170 --> 00:07:08.270 align:middle line:10%
[SPEAKING IN FRENCH]

00:07:08.270 --> 00:07:09.950 align:middle line:10%


00:07:09.950 --> 00:07:12.200 align:middle line:10%
Life is no brief candle to me.

00:07:12.200 --> 00:07:13.655 align:middle line:10%
[SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

00:07:13.655 --> 00:07:16.660 align:middle line:90%


00:07:16.660 --> 00:07:18.020 align:middle line:10%
[SPEAKING IN FRENCH]

00:07:18.020 --> 00:07:19.750 align:middle line:10%


00:07:19.750 --> 00:07:23.820 align:middle line:10%
Before handing it on
to future generations.

00:07:23.820 --> 00:07:25.240 align:middle line:10%
George Bernard Shaw.

00:07:25.240 --> 00:07:29.350 align:middle line:90%


00:07:29.350 --> 00:07:34.080 align:middle line:10%
I don't think an authentic
stand comes from your head.

00:07:34.080 --> 00:07:35.950 align:middle line:10%
I think an authentic stand
comes from your heart.

00:07:35.950 --> 00:07:39.770 align:middle line:90%


00:07:39.770 --> 00:07:48.670 align:middle line:84%
If your child is sick,
something happens in you to make

00:07:48.670 --> 00:07:52.896 align:middle line:90%
a miracle, to make a miracle.

00:07:52.896 --> 00:07:57.950 align:middle line:84%
And if you start thinking
about it, you'll sit down.

00:07:57.950 --> 00:08:01.010 align:middle line:84%
But if you feel it,
you'll stand up.

00:08:01.010 --> 00:08:03.450 align:middle line:84%
That's the amazing
thing about this thing

00:08:03.450 --> 00:08:06.780 align:middle line:84%
is that it's, when you
stand up, you license

00:08:06.780 --> 00:08:08.510 align:middle line:90%
other people to stand up.

00:08:08.510 --> 00:08:09.880 align:middle line:84%
Now you standing up
by yourself don't

00:08:09.880 --> 00:08:13.225 align:middle line:84%
make a dadgum bit of difference
in the rational world.

00:08:13.225 --> 00:08:15.950 align:middle line:90%
You just one fool standing up.

00:08:15.950 --> 00:08:18.190 align:middle line:84%
But have you ever seen
a standing ovation?

00:08:18.190 --> 00:08:20.852 align:middle line:84%
It starts with one
fool standing up.

00:08:20.852 --> 00:08:23.610 align:middle line:84%
And then pretty soon, the
whole stadium is standing up.

00:08:23.610 --> 00:08:25.598 align:middle line:90%
And it's a different moment.

00:08:25.598 --> 00:08:27.550 align:middle line:90%
[CROWD CHEERING]

00:08:27.550 --> 00:08:34.400 align:middle line:90%


00:08:34.400 --> 00:08:36.409 align:middle line:90%
You know, I've got a hunch.

00:08:36.409 --> 00:08:38.740 align:middle line:84%
One of the things that
unites all of us in this room

00:08:38.740 --> 00:08:42.740 align:middle line:84%
is the desire to have
our lives have meaning.

00:08:42.740 --> 00:08:44.700 align:middle line:84%
And there's a way
of orienting to that

00:08:44.700 --> 00:08:46.510 align:middle line:90%
that I'm going to share now.

00:08:46.510 --> 00:08:49.190 align:middle line:90%
And it's to take a stand.

00:08:49.190 --> 00:08:52.170 align:middle line:84%
To take a stand for something,
to say that I'm for something.

00:08:52.170 --> 00:08:54.190 align:middle line:90%
A stand is to be for something.

00:08:54.190 --> 00:08:57.640 align:middle line:84%
It's not to be against something
else and it's not to be right.

00:08:57.640 --> 00:09:02.470 align:middle line:84%
It's just to have your life make
sense in support of something

00:09:02.470 --> 00:09:03.640 align:middle line:90%
that you affirm.

00:09:03.640 --> 00:09:09.380 align:middle line:84%
It's a way of moving from soul
from heart, not from the head,

00:09:09.380 --> 00:09:13.610 align:middle line:84%
towards something that
we firmly believe in.

00:09:13.610 --> 00:09:15.980 align:middle line:84%
And now here we are,
we're gathered together

00:09:15.980 --> 00:09:18.110 align:middle line:84%
by the purpose of
this symposium,

00:09:18.110 --> 00:09:19.610 align:middle line:84%
bringing forth an
environmentally

00:09:19.610 --> 00:09:23.370 align:middle line:84%
sustainable, spiritually
fulfilling, socially just human

00:09:23.370 --> 00:09:25.720 align:middle line:90%
presence.

00:09:25.720 --> 00:09:28.300 align:middle line:84%
And I want to offer all
of us the opportunity

00:09:28.300 --> 00:09:34.970 align:middle line:84%
now to take a stand in our lives
that affirm that, that purpose.

00:09:34.970 --> 00:09:36.450 align:middle line:84%
And so Anita's going
to come and join

00:09:36.450 --> 00:09:41.701 align:middle line:84%
us and lead us just through the
opportunity to declare a stand.

00:09:41.701 --> 00:09:44.060 align:middle line:84%
Thanks.
Do you mind passing those out?

00:09:44.060 --> 00:09:47.270 align:middle line:84%
So what John is passing
out is a declaration card.

00:09:47.270 --> 00:09:53.440 align:middle line:84%
And I filled out one of
these four years ago.

00:09:53.440 --> 00:09:56.760 align:middle line:10%
And on the front is the
purpose of the symposium,

00:09:56.760 --> 00:09:59.430 align:middle line:10%
the commitment of bringing
forth an environmentally

00:09:59.430 --> 00:10:02.590 align:middle line:10%
sustainable, spiritually
fulfilling and socially

00:10:02.590 --> 00:10:04.270 align:middle line:10%
just human presence.

00:10:04.270 --> 00:10:07.370 align:middle line:10%
And on the back is the George
Bernard Shaw quote that you

00:10:07.370 --> 00:10:10.358 align:middle line:10%
just heard on the video.

00:10:10.358 --> 00:10:12.970 align:middle line:84%
You know, we all
have the opportunity

00:10:12.970 --> 00:10:17.780 align:middle line:84%
to say what our life is about,
what we stand for, who we are.

00:10:17.780 --> 00:10:20.180 align:middle line:84%
And I've found that the
power of taking a stand

00:10:20.180 --> 00:10:26.510 align:middle line:84%
is larger, greater, more
potent than I ever thought.

00:10:26.510 --> 00:10:29.270 align:middle line:84%
When we take a stand,
we move from having

00:10:29.270 --> 00:10:33.660 align:middle line:84%
a point of view about the world
to actually having vision.

00:10:33.660 --> 00:10:37.570 align:middle line:84%
And from vision, your
life can really matter.

00:10:37.570 --> 00:10:39.790 align:middle line:84%
You can really
make a difference.

00:10:39.790 --> 00:10:42.140 align:middle line:84%
I invite you to take out
your declaration card

00:10:42.140 --> 00:10:45.530 align:middle line:84%
and to sign it, affirming
your own commitment

00:10:45.530 --> 00:10:47.620 align:middle line:84%
to an environmentally
sustainable,

00:10:47.620 --> 00:10:50.460 align:middle line:84%
spiritually fulfilling,
socially just

00:10:50.460 --> 00:10:54.010 align:middle line:90%
human presence on this planet.

00:10:54.010 --> 00:10:55.900 align:middle line:84%
Whether you sign this
declaration or not

00:10:55.900 --> 00:10:57.550 align:middle line:90%
is up to you.

00:10:57.550 --> 00:10:59.950 align:middle line:84%
But if you do sign
the card, I suggest

00:10:59.950 --> 00:11:02.610 align:middle line:84%
you put it up somewhere
at home or at your office

00:11:02.610 --> 00:11:04.220 align:middle line:90%
where you'll see it.

00:11:04.220 --> 00:11:06.710 align:middle line:84%
It will remind you of
your personal commitment

00:11:06.710 --> 00:11:10.295 align:middle line:84%
to be an agent of change in
the world, a global citizen who

00:11:10.295 --> 00:11:13.940 align:middle line:84%
is working to shift the course
of history, turn the tide

00:11:13.940 --> 00:11:18.210 align:middle line:84%
and transform our future
into the one we want.

00:11:18.210 --> 00:11:22.560 align:middle line:84%
Once you take this stand, your
life will never be the same.

00:11:22.560 --> 00:11:25.820 align:middle line:90%
I know, because I did it.

